# Metric Resource: SemanticCosineSimilarity
<https://w3id.org/soel/metric/SemanticCosineSimilarity> a dqv:Metric ;

    dcterms:identifier "https://w3id.org/soel/metric/SemanticCosineSimilarity" ;
    dcterms:title "Semantic distances of dense vector representation using pretrained encoder."@en ;
    rdfs:label "SemanticCosineSimilarity: Semantic distances of dense vector representation using pretrained encoder."^^xsd:string ;
    vivo:abbreviation "semantic_model-id"^^xsd:string ;
    dcat:version "0.0.1"^^xsd:string ;
    ftr:status "Active"@en ;
    dcat:landingPage <https://w3id.org/soel/metric/SemanticCosineSimilarity> ;

    # Descriptive Content
    dcterms:description """
This metric aims to evaluate if the generated label semantically aligned with any existing label in the gold standard ontology.

**Calculation Process:**

1. Select a pre-trained semantic natural language encoder.

2. Encoding the generated label and gold standard ontology into vectors.

3. Calculate the cosine similarity between the generated label vector and vectors in the gold standard ontology.

4. Range of the semantic cosine similarity is between 0 and 1; Noted higher value indicate better match.

**Example:**

Encoder: mxbai-embed-large

Generate_Label_1: hasWine 

Generate_Label_2: wine

Generate_Label_3: hasLiquor 

Gold_Standard_Label: Has Wine

Result: 

1. SemanticCosineSimilarity(Encoder(Generate_Label_1), Encoder(Gold_Standard_Label)) = 0.7772
2. SemanticCosineSimilarity(Encoder(Generate_Label_2), Encoder(Gold_Standard_Label)) = 0.8840
3. SemanticCosineSimilarity(Encoder(Generate_Label_3), Encoder(Gold_Standard_Label)) = 0.4690

**What is being measured?**

This metric captures meaning-level correspondence between generated label and labels in gold standard ontology. 
""" ;
    dcat:keyword "Ontology Concept Matching"@en ;
    dcat:keyword "Metric"@en ;
    dcat:keyword "Classes"@en ;
    
